==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bridle iron
<hw>Bri"dle i`ron</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A strong
flat bar of iron, so bent as to support, as in a stirrup, one end of a
floor timber, etc., where no sufficient bearing can be had; -- called
also <altname>stirrup</altname> and <altname>hanger</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bridler</ent>⟦br⟧
